            <h2>How the Japanese Name Converter Works</h2>
            <p>Our Japanese name converter uses phonetic transliteration to convert your English name into three Japanese writing systems. When you enter your name, the tool maps each English syllable to its closest Japanese phonetic equivalent, following standard Hepburn romanization rules used in Japan for foreign names.</p>

            <p>Foreign names in Japan are traditionally written in <strong>Katakana</strong> (カタカナ), the syllabary specifically designed for loanwords, foreign names, and onomatopoeia. Our converter also generates <strong>Hiragana</strong> (ひらがな) and <strong>Kanji</strong> (漢字) representations using ateji — kanji characters selected for their phonetic readings rather than semantic meaning.</p>

            <h3>Japanese Writing Systems Explained</h3>
            <div class="writing-systems">
                <div class="ws-card">
